24/09/2003
NEW YORK, United States -- Macedonian President Boris Trajkovski reiterated on Tuesday (23 September) his country's willingness to contribute to the international fight against terrorism. Addressing an international anti-terrorism conference in New York within the framework of the annual UN General Assembly session, Trajkovski also called for a readjusted international policy against terrorism, explaining it cannot be fought using only traditional means. He also urged faster adoption of the UN conventions against terrorism and nuclear terrorism. Trajkovski was the only Southeast European leader to participate in the forum. (MIA, A1 TV - 23/09/03)
